    },
    {
      "id": "detailed_3_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "detailed_3",
      "description": "Older car in fair, driver-quality condition being listed honestly. It appears complete and usable, with the kind of visible age, wear, and cosmetic imperfections you would expect from an older vehicle that has been driven and not fully restored. The paint, body, trim, and interior should be considered presentable but not show-quality, and buyers should expect some blemishes, wear, and general aging throughout. This is not a perfect example, but it looks like a solid candidate for someone who wants an affordable older car to enjoy, improve over time, or use as a light project rather than taking on a full restoration. A reasonable expectation is a car that can be enjoyed as-is with ongoing sorting, maintenance, and attention typical of an older vehicle.",
